      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "=== DGX Spark PuLID identity + ReferenceLatentPlus outfit v1 ===\nPurpose: best-practice role separation after stock ReferenceLatent tests failed to separate identity face from identity clothing.\n\nCreated on 2026-06-07:\n- ID image is not connected to ReferenceLatent or ReferenceLatentPlus.\n- ID image is used only by PuLID-Flux2, so it contributes face identity rather than clothing.\n- Outfit/pose image is used only by ReferenceLatentPlus.\n- ReferenceLatentPlus image_1 uses body+clothes+background, face/hair disabled.\n- ReferenceLatentPlus strength 1.30, max reference cap 1.20 MP, mask_fill_mode pixel_grey, timestep 0.00 to 0.95.\n- PuLID model: pulid_flux2_klein_v2.safetensors.\n- PuLID strength starts at 1.10; if face is weak, test 1.20 then 1.40.\n- Keeps Turbo r128 at 0.45.\n- Keeps SNOFS omitted for this test.\n- Flux2KleinEnhancer remains absent.\n- Keeps the proven two-stage sampler: dpmpp_2m / sgm_uniform / 10 steps / SplitSigmas 6.\n\nRequired custom nodes and model assets:\n- ComfyUI-PuLID-Flux2 with pulid_flux2_klein_v2.safetensors and InsightFace/EVA-CLIP dependencies.\n- comfyui-ReferenceLatentPlus with MediaPipe installed for auto masks.\n\nDecision rule: if face identity works and clothing improves but pose remains weak, add DWPose/OpenPose next. If ReferenceLatentPlus is missing, install it before running this workflow."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
